title: For Sale:  Swiss K31
postcontent: Used K31 in good condition.  As shown in second picture is a small arsenal repair.  It is very common for these rifles to have some sort of repair done to their stocks, this one is a reasonably small repair compared to others I have seen.This rifle's serial number dates it to 1944.  It is a straight pull bolt rifle, very well made.  It has a walnut stock as is usual for a pre-1946 model year.  It does have a trooper tag under the buttplate.  These rifles have two stage triggers, there is a long take up and then a very clean break.  If you haven't shot one of these, the ammo is similar to shooting very hot 308 Win, and the straight pull bolt allows for very fast follow up shots.This rifle was fed GP11 and Prvi Partisan ammunition, but takes standard .308 bullets if you are a reloader.  (I do have all of the necessary dies)I have many more pictures of this rifle I can't put on this listing, if you are interested in seeing more of them email me.To ship to FFL goes about $40 to the lower 48 if you want to go down that route, any transfer fees on your side would be up to you.
